I went for nobility and duty. Strider/Aragorn. Henry V. Charlton Heston
in El Cid. I didn't care what they looked like as long as their ideals were
lofty and they were steadfast. Which Beatle did I like best? John Lennon.

messages.messageBody:
on 12/21/01 10:00 AM, Pam Hartley at pamhartley@... wrote:

> Ah, now see, I always wonder if we can tell things about each other by who
> we had crushes on as young to middle teens.
>
> Some of us (raises hand) liked the bad-good boys (Han Solo). Some of us (my
> sister) liked the androgynous too-good boys (Luke).
>
> I married a guy who looks like a bad boy. My sister married two Malibu Kens
> in a row. <g>
>
> Pam

OK, so which Beatle did you like best?

My friend, Merry, and I found we had a weirdness in common: We both liked
Ringo best, and couldn't stand Paul. Same with the Monkees: We liked
Mickey best, couldn't stand whichever one was the cutiepie -- Davy?
Drummers rule.

These weren't teen crushes, of course; more like 2nd grade in the case of
the Beatles (remember the cartoon show??), and 5th grade for the Monkees.
David Cassidy, Bobby Sherman, the Archies, those guys were 6th grade and I
HATED 'em. My first celebrity crush was Chad Everett.

Star Wars was college era for me... Han Solo, sigh.

And I married a guy who looked like Gilligan. (Well, that was my first
impression <g> Don't tell!)


I really should be doing laundry and baking cookies right now!
Nancy

(and yeah, I just noticed how my memory's timeline is tied to
school...bleah.)
